                            <comment id="15393980" author="slebresne" created="Tue, 26 Jul 2016 15:48:49 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The assertion is due to the code in &lt;tt&gt;DataResolver&lt;/tt&gt; mistakenly assuming a marker is open when it may not. But this is actually a manifestation of a larger problem, which is that the code in &lt;tt&gt;DataResolver&lt;/tt&gt; dealing with range tombstone is incorrect (it doesn&apos;t compute read-repair correctly). In fact, the &lt;tt&gt;MergeListener&lt;/tt&gt; interface that it uses isn&apos;t providing enough information for it to do its job properly. Attaching a patch that solves that, including a new unit test that both reproduce the assertion of this ticket, but also shows the code wasn&apos;t doing what it should have in the first place.&lt;/p&gt;

